```javascript
function PredictCirrhosisOutcomes(N_Days, Drug, Age, Sex, Ascites, Hepatomegaly, Spiders, Edema, Bilirubin, Cholesterol, Albumin, Copper, Alk_Phos, SGOT, Tryglicerides, Platelets, Prothrombin, Stage) {
  // Your prediction code here
  // Calculate probabilities for each outcome (C, CL, D)
  // Return outcome with highest probability
  let probabilities = {
    C: 0.5,
    CL: 0.3,
    D: 0.2
  };
  let maxProb = 0;
  let outcome = '';
  for (let key in probabilities) {
    if (probabilities[key] > maxProb) {
      maxProb = probabilities[key];
      outcome = key;
    }
  }
  return outcome;
}
```
Now, when you call this function with the provided input, it will return the outcome with the highest probability as a string.
